Tickets start at $20 for a spot on the lawn and run up to $5000 for benefactors, who get a seat in the open-air auditorium. Bacall and soprano Barbara Hendricks will perform a movement from Bernstein's Symphony No. The Leonard Bernstein Gala Birthday Performance is a benefit concert scheduled for the composer's 70th birthday, Aug 25, to raise money for the Tanglewood Music Center, where Bernstein got his conducting start. Beverly Sills, Lauren Bacall, Betty Comden and Phyllis Newman are among performers who will sing, act and make guest appearances at a birthday bash in August for conductor Leonard Bernstein. 